co.cask.coopr.http.handler

Class AdminHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • co.cask.http.AbstractHttpHandler
      • co.cask.coopr.http.handler.AbstractAuthHandler
        • co.cask.coopr.http.handler.AdminHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    co.cask.http.HttpHandler

    @Path(value="/v2")
public class AdminHandler
extends AbstractAuthHandler
    Handler for getting, adding, modifying, and deleting admin defined entities. GET calls work for any user, non-GET calls work only for admin.

      • getQueueMetrics

        @GET
@Path(value="/metrics/queues")
public void getQueueMetrics(org.jboss.netty.handler.codec.http.HttpRequest request,
                            co.cask.http.HttpResponder responder)
        Get a mapping of tenant to provisioner queue metrics for that tenant. User requesting the metrics must be a tenant, with tenant admins getting back only the queue metrics for their own tenant and with superadmins getting the metrics across all tenants.
        Parameters:
        request - Request for queue metrics.
        responder - Responder for sending the response.
